# RSAI Click — Linktree/s.id Clone Application

Build a **link-in-bio** application (like Linktree, s.id) on top of the existing rsai-click TanStack Start project. Users can create personalized pages with multiple links, share them via a short URL, and track click analytics.

## User Review Required

> [!NOTE]
> **Database** via Docker Compose (MariaDB 11 + Adminer). Jalankan `docker compose up -d`.

> [!NOTE]
> **Authentication** menggunakan [better-auth](https://better-auth.com) dengan Drizzle adapter + TanStack Start integration. Fitur: email/password login, session management, route protection.

> [!WARNING]
> **Existing starter code** (component-example, about page) akan dihapus/diganti.

---

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Docker Compose (MariaDB)

#### [NEW] [docker-compose.yml](file:///d:/project-rsai/rsai-click/docker-compose.yml)
- MariaDB 11 + Adminer
- Credentials: `root` / `rsai_click_pwd`, database: `rsai_click`
- Ports: MariaDB `3306`, Adminer `8080`

#### [NEW] [.env](file:///d:/project-rsai/rsai-click/.env)
```
DATABASE_URL=mysql://root:rsai_click_pwd@localhost:3306/rsai_click
BETTER_AUTH_SECRET=<random-secret>
BETTER_AUTH_URL=http://localhost:3000
```

---

### 2. Database Layer (Drizzle ORM + MariaDB)

#### [NEW] [drizzle.config.ts](file:///d:/project-rsai/rsai-click/drizzle.config.ts)
- Drizzle Kit config → MariaDB, schema path

#### [NEW] [src/db/index.ts](file:///d:/project-rsai/rsai-click/src/db/index.ts)
- `mysql2` pool connection + Drizzle ORM instance export

#### [NEW] [src/db/schema.ts](file:///d:/project-rsai/rsai-click/src/db/schema.ts)

| Table | Columns |
|-------|---------|
| `pages` | `id`, `user_id` (FK→user), `slug` (unique), `title`, `bio`, `avatar_url`, `theme`, `is_active`, `created_at`, `updated_at` |
| `links` | `id`, `page_id` (FK→pages), `title`, `url`, `icon`, `position`, `is_active`, `created_at`, `updated_at` |
| `clicks` | `id`, `link_id` (FK→links), `ip_address`, `user_agent`, `referer`, `clicked_at` |

> [!NOTE]
> Better-auth auto-generates `user`, `session`, `verification`, `account` tables via CLI.

---

### 3. Authentication (better-auth)

#### [NEW] [src/lib/auth.ts](file:///d:/project-rsai/rsai-click/src/lib/auth.ts)
- Server-side better-auth instance
- Drizzle adapter with `provider: "mysql"`
- `tanstackStartCookies()` plugin
- Email/password auth enabled

#### [NEW] [src/lib/auth-client.ts](file:///d:/project-rsai/rsai-click/src/lib/auth-client.ts)
- Client-side `createAuthClient()` for React

#### [NEW] [src/lib/auth.server.ts](file:///d:/project-rsai/rsai-click/src/lib/auth.server.ts)
- `getSession()` + `ensureSession()` server functions using `createServerFn`
- Used in route `beforeLoad` for protection

#### [NEW] [src/routes/api/auth/$.ts](file:///d:/project-rsai/rsai-click/src/routes/api/auth/$.ts)
- Mount better-auth handler at `/api/auth/*`

#### [NEW] [src/routes/login.tsx](file:///d:/project-rsai/rsai-click/src/routes/login.tsx)
- Login page with email/password form
- Redirect to `/admin` on success

#### [NEW] [src/routes/register.tsx](file:///d:/project-rsai/rsai-click/src/routes/register.tsx)
- Registration page with email/password/name form
- Redirect to `/admin` on success

---

### 4. Server Functions (API)

#### [NEW] [src/server/pages.ts](file:///d:/project-rsai/rsai-click/src/server/pages.ts)
- `getPages()`, `getPageById(id)`, `getPageBySlug(slug)`, `createPage(data)`, `updatePage(id, data)`, `deletePage(id)`
- All mutations protected with `ensureSession()`
- Pages scoped to authenticated user's `user_id`

#### [NEW] [src/server/links.ts](file:///d:/project-rsai/rsai-click/src/server/links.ts)
- `getLinksByPageId(pageId)`, `createLink(data)`, `updateLink(id, data)`, `deleteLink(id)`, `reorderLinks(pageId, orderedIds)`

#### [NEW] [src/server/clicks.ts](file:///d:/project-rsai/rsai-click/src/server/clicks.ts)
- `trackClick(linkId, metadata)`, `getClickStats(pageId)`

